    {
      "repo": "github.com/sg-evals/libreoffice-core--9c8b85f3",
      "path": "include/sfx2/app.hxx",
      "symbol": "SfxApplication"
    }
  ],
  "text": "The core LibreOffice document model architecture is defined by these key C++ classes:\n\n1. **SfxObjectShell** (include/sfx2/objsh.hxx:182) - The base document shell class that all document types inherit from. This is the fundamental framework class for managing document persistence, UI, and lifecycle.\n\n2. **SwDoc** (sw/inc/doc.hxx:196) - The Writer (word processor) document class. Represents the model of a Writer document and manages all document-related data and operations for text documents.\n\n3. **ScDocument** (sc/inc/document.hxx:331) - The Calc (spreadsheet) document class. The central class representing a spreadsheet document with all its cells, sheets, and data.\n\n4. **SdDrawDocument** (sd/inc/drawdoc.hxx:338) - The Impress/Draw document class. The document model for presentations and drawing documents, inheriting from FmFormModel.\n\n5. **SfxApplication** (include/sfx2/app.hxx:103) - The LibreOffice application framework entry point. This is the main application singleton class that manages the overall application lifecycle, windows, and document windows.\n\nThese classes form a hierarchical architecture where SfxObjectShell is the base, and document-specific classes (SwDoc, ScDocument, SdDrawDocument) inherit from it through their respective document shells (SwDocShell, ScDocShell, SdDrawDocShell). SfxApplication manages the overall application context and coordinates all these document shells."
}

